==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interscendent
<hw>In`ter*scend"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Inter-</er>, and <er>Ascend</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<def>Having exponents which are radical quantities; -- said of certain
powers; <as>as, <mathex>x<exp>⟦root⟧2</exp></mathex>, or
<mathex>x<exp>⟦root⟧a</exp></mathex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Interscendent series</b></col>, <cd>a series whose terms
are interscendent quantities.</cd> <rj><au>Hutton.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interscind</ent>⟦br⟧
